    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-07T16:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-07T16:45:00-05:00" n="804"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/602: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-07T16:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 8, 12.05 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed that Julio Acosta and men now occupy Pena Blanca, Costa Rica, and
                    he has been proclaimed Provisional President. They have telegraphed President
                    Chamorro requesting that they be recognized as belligerents.</p>
                <p>No skirmishes reported between contending parties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
